PTE: Page Table Entry
PTBR: Page Table Base Register

CISC: Complex Instruction Set Computer -> easy to use?
RISC: Reduced Instruction Set Computer -> simple instruction?

TLB: Translation Lookaside Buffer

TLB valid bit: Refers to whether the TLB entry has a valid translation within
               it, which is different from page table valid bit. By default,
               the TLB entry is set to invalid.

Exceeding the TLB coverage means that the number of pages that a program
accesses in short period of time exceeds the number of pages that fit into TLB,
and the program will generate a lot of TLB misses and will be a bit slower.
